Field Name] Following the field name is a sequence of lines. The lines may be in any order unless there is a multiple entry in the section. In this case, the enties which repeat must appear in consequative order. The other entries and the placement of the block of multiple entries can be ordered as one wishes. However, if the AR system description is for a new system, the order of the entries will be reflected in the format of the AR files.  Each line contains the name of the attribute, followed by a colon, then the attribute value:  Attribute: value  The attribute that is required for all fields is type. The type attribute must take one of the following values: ARId, DateTime, Enumerated, BoundedString, or UnboundedString. If the type of the field is BoundedString, the field description must contain a MaxLength attribute. This attribute takes a cardinal value, and it is the maxmimum length of the bounded-length string.If the type of the field is Enumerated, the field description must contain a set of EnumeratedItem attributes. These attributes describe the values that the Enumerated field can take. (The value NIL is always a legal value for any Enumerated field and is implicit in the description.) There may be an arbitrary number of EnumeratedItem attributes per enumerated field, but they must appear consequatively in the field description. The value of the attribute is a record. The record must contain a name field, which is a quoted string containing the name of the enumeration value. The record also must contain a key value, which is a cardinal value. The key value 0 is reserved for the Nil enumerated value:  EnumeratedItem: [name: "Dog", key: 3] Enumerated field descriptions must also contain a DependsOn attribute. The value of a DependsOn attribute is a record containing the name of the field which it depends on and the item in the field which this particular section is depending upon.  If the field does not depend upon another enumerated then these value are NIL.  DependsOn: [field: NIL, item: NIL] --no dependency  DependsOn: [field: System, item: Communication] --depends EnumeratedItem          Communication in the System field	  A Enumerated field description which dpends on another almost always wants to describe more than one set of EnumeratedItem attributes. I.e. it wants to describe one set of attributes per dependent item.  To do this multiply declare the field with a different DependsOn attribute. [SubSystem]Type: EnumeratedDependsOn: [field: System, item: Communication]EnumeratedItem: [name: "Communication Tools", key: 11]EnumeratedItem: [name: Courier, key: 12]EnumeratedItem: [name: Drivers, key: 13]EnumeratedItem: [name: Transport, key: 14]EnumeratedItem: [name: RS232C, key: 15]EnumeratedItem: [name: Other, key: 16][SubSystem]Type: EnumeratedDependsOn: [field: System, item: Diagnostics]EnumeratedItem: [name: "Acceptance Tests", key: 17]EnumeratedItem: [name: Boot, key: 18]EnumeratedItem: [name: "Extended Isolation", key: 19]EnumeratedItem: [name: "Magnetic Tape", key: 20]EnumeratedItem: [name: Online, key: 21]EnumeratedItem: [name: Preboot, key: 22]EnumeratedItem: [name: Other, key: 23]  A field description may also contain a set of Default attributes for specifying default values for the field any of the released Adobe Tools. The value of these attributes is a record containing the tool name which should represent the default and the default value.Default: [tool: Submit, default: TimeOfDay]The value of the defualt may be any legal value of the corresponding type. In addition, there are two distinguished values that the system recognizes. The string "CurrentTOD" is the current time of day, and the string "LoginName" is the name of the logged-in user.AR System Descriptions and the Adobe Admin Tool.Although it is possible to create an AR System Description completely by hand, the Adobe Admin Tool provides some assistance in creating and analyzing new versions of AR System Descriptions. In particular, it is possible to give the Adobe Admin Tool a "loosely bound" version of the description, that is, one for which not all enumerated items have key fields in their value records. The Adobe Admin Tool will compare this description with the currently installed version of the system and fill in these values so as to match the existing system as much as possible and to minimize the amount of data manipulation needed to convert to the new system. It also generates the UsedEnumeratedValues entries to reflect the update. In order to install a new version of an AR System, however, all these values must be present in the system description.   [BNF description]Example: The following AR System Description describes part of the System Software AR System. [SystemParams]SystemName: "AdobeTest"UsedEnumeratedValues: 1-39Host: "Rasp:OSBU North:Xerox"Directory: "NSAdobeTest"Version: 1NumberOfFields: 22 [Number]Type: ARId[Date]Type: DateTimeDefault: [tool: Submit, default: CurrentTOD][Originator]Type: BoundedStringMaxLength: 20Default: [tool: Submit, default: LoginName][System]Type: EnumeratedDependsOn: [field: NIL, item: NIL]EnumeratedItem: [name: Communication, key: 1]EnumeratedItem: [name: Diagnostics, key: 2]EnumeratedItem: [name: Documentation, key: 3]EnumeratedItem: [name: Environment, key: 4]EnumeratedItem: [name: "Mesa Tools", key: 5]EnumeratedItem: [name: Microcode, key: 6]EnumeratedItem: [name: "Microcode Tools", key: 7]EnumeratedItem: [name: Pilot, key: 8]EnumeratedItem: [name: "Other Tools", key: 9]EnumeratedItem: [name: Other, key: 10][SubSystem]Type: EnumeratedDependsOn: [field: System, item: Communication]EnumeratedItem: [name: "Communication Tools", key: 11]EnumeratedItem: [name: Courier, key: 12]EnumeratedItem: [name: Drivers, key: 13]EnumeratedItem: [name: Transport, key: 14]EnumeratedItem: [name: RS232C, key: 15]EnumeratedItem: [name: Other, key: 16][SubSystem]Type: Enumera